        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/b9bd4f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2024-05-14T15:54:27.473Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Great notes, Alex. Maybe the most impressive Cali cab I\u2019ve ever had was a Mayacamas from the mid-late 60s (sorry can\u2019t remember exactly!) about 15 years ago. A friend opened it for me, blind, and I remember wondering whether to guess 59 or 61 Latour.</p>\n<p>More recently I enjoyed the 83, which was also just stellar.</p>\n<p>The only downside is they take FOREVER to come around.</p>\n<p>The property is awesome too, way up on the mountain. Requires a real commitment to get there - def not recommended after multiple winery visits!</p>",
